gw.api.json.mapping

Interface TransformResultValue


  • public interface TransformResultValue
    The result of a mapping transform() call for a single schema property.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      @Nullable JsonSchemaProperty getSchemaProperty()
      The JsonSchemaProperty associated with this value
      @Nullable java.lang.String getTransformErrorMessage()
      Returns the error message, if any, describing the error that happened as the result was transformed
      @Nullable java.lang.Exception getTransformException()
      Returns the exception, if any, that occurred during transform of the value
      @Nullable java.lang.Object getValue()
      The actual value for this property; this could either be a scalar value such as a String or Integer, another TransformResult object (if isObject() is true), a List (if isObjectArray() is true), or a List of scalars (if isScalarArray()) is true.
      boolean hasLocalError()
      Returns true if there was an error during the transform of this value
      boolean hasLocalOrNestedErrors()
      Returns true if there was an error during the transform of this value or any nested TransformResult(s) this value may contain
      boolean isObject()
      Returns true if this value represents an object property, i.e. a nested TransformResult
      boolean isObjectArray()
      Returns true if this value represents an "object array" property, in this case a List of nested TransformResults
      boolean isScalar()
      Returns true if this value represents a scalar property
      boolean isScalarArray()
      Returns true if this value represents a "scalar array" property, in this case a List of Objects

      • getSchemaProperty

      • getValue

        @Nullable
@Nullable java.lang.Object getValue()
        The actual value for this property; this could either be a scalar value such as a String or Integer, another TransformResult object (if isObject() is true), a List (if isObjectArray() is true), or a List of scalars (if isScalarArray()) is true. If the original path expression that created this TransformResultValue evaluated to null, getValue() will either return null (if this represents a scalar or single object in the schema) or an empty list (if this represents an array of objects or scalars in the schema). If isErrant() is true, however, the value may be empty even for array properties.
